4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Existing law provides that in certain
6 circumstances a child or a spouse of a law enforcement
7 officer who is killed or totally disabled in the line
8 of duty may receive financial assistance to pay college
9 tuition.
10 This bill would establish a program to pay
11 tuition and associated expenses on behalf of children
12 and spouses of long-term city, county, and state law
13 enforcement officers. This bill would provide that the
14 scholarship money may be used for an undergraduate
15 course of study offered by a public or private
16 technical school, college, or university in the State
17 of Alabama.
18 This bill would further provide for the
19 administration of this scholarship by the Alabama
20 Commission on Higher Education; require annual
21 reporting on the program to the Legislature; and
22 establish the Alabama Law Enforcement Officers' Family
23 Scholarship Fund.
24 This bill would also authorize creation by the
25 Department of Revenue of a blackout license plate,
26 proceeds for which would be used to fund the
27 scholarship.
28
