169 residency in the state.
170 (3) That the recipient completes the academic terms for
171 which the scholarship is available pursuant to Section
172 36-11-222(a) within 66 months of the approval of the
173 application, in the absence of a formal waiver of this
174 condition by the commission due to injury, illness, the
175 necessity of part-time enrollment, or some other extraordinary
176 circumstance.
177 (b) If the recipient's eligibility is based on spousal
178 status, eligibility shall end if the marriage to the
179 qualifying law enforcement officer is terminated by a decree
180 of divorce or, in the case of a recipient who is a surviving
181 spouse, remarriage.
182 (c) A recipient may maintain eligibility for the
183 scholarship while changing his or her approved postsecondary
184 program or transferring to another participating institution,
185 or both, only if the change or transfer is approved by the
186 appropriate participating institution no later than the
187 beginning of the fifth semester or the ninth quarter for which
188 the scholarship would be available.
