239 Section 2. (a) Notwithstanding Sections 32-6-64,
240 32-6-67, and 32-6-68, upon application to the judge of probate
241 or license commissioner, compliance with motor vehicle
242 registration and licensing laws, payment of regular fees
243 required by law for license plates for private passenger or
244 pleasure motor vehicles or motorcycles, and payment of an
245 additional annual fee of fifty dollars ($50), owners of motor
246 vehicles or motorcycles who are residents of Alabama shall
247 upon request be issued a personalized blackout license plate.
248 (b) The additional blackout license plate fee shall be
249 distributed in the following manner:
250 (1) Two and one-half percent commission, provided by
251 Section 40-12-269(a)(1).
252 (2) Manufacturing costs of one dollar and fifty cents
